{"body": "I'm not sure there are enough use-cases for this option. Consider the situation where your model is in a different namespace than your controller, this would lead to a new option. \r\n\r\nMaybe we could introduce something to specify the name of the model to use. This would apply to more uses:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrails g scaffold_controller Admin::User --model-name=\"User\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n@rafaelfranca @carlosantoniodasilva what do you think?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/20869320", "created_at": "2013-07-12T10:30:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11408#issuecomment-20869320", "updated_at": "2013-07-12T10:30:01Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11408, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/senny", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd1359f9934ee5a75ed441ffce412a0a1.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "senny", "type": "User", "id": 5402, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d527bd3543c151008190"}, "id": 20869320, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11408"}
